burn.t.sol
├── given delegate called
│  └── it should revert
└── given not delegate called
   ├── when the id references a null stream
   │  └── it should revert
   └── given the id does not reference a null stream
      ├── given the stream has not been depleted
      │  ├── when the stream's status is "PENDING"
      │  │  └── it should revert
      │  ├── when the stream's status is "STREAMING"
      │  │  └── it should revert
      │  ├── when the stream's status is "SETTLED"
      │  │  └── it should revert
      │  └── when the stream's status is "CANCELED"
      │     └── it should revert
      └── given the stream has been depleted
         ├── when the caller is unauthorized
         │  └── it should revert
         └── given the caller is authorized
            ├── when NFT does not exist
            │  └── it should revert
            └── given NFT exists
               ├── when the caller is an approved third party
               │  └── it should burn the NFT
               └── when the caller is the owner of the NFT
                  └── it should burn the NFT
